title: Fighter jets return to Stuart Air Show
text: Supersonic fighter jets return to Stuart Air Show Oct. 30-Nov.1 Ginny Beagan 12:05 PM, Oct 19, 2015 38 mins ago stuart | family fun | tcpalm social | entertainment | local news The US Air Force F-16, known as the “Fighting Falcon, will give a high flying demonstration and take part in the moving Heritage Flight with a P-51 Mustang Oct. 31 and Nov. 1 at the Stuart Air Show. (PHOTO PROVIDED BY STUART AIR SHOW ) Tech. Sgt. Benjamin Wilson The US Army Golden Knights, considered the world’s best parachute team, will make their first appearance at the Stuart Air Show this weekend. (PHOTO PROVIDED BY STUART AIR SHOW) Airman 1st Class Shane Karp A U.S. Navy F-18E Super Hornet will do a flying demonstration Oct. 31 and Nov. 1 over the skies of Stuart. (PHOTO PROVIDED BY STUART AIR SHOW) Staff Sgt. Shawn Nickel
